{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsZMzYgCv3dGYeknm5DJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Job completed cleanly with no memory errors: `Pi is roughly 3.1414662228293246` and `spark_etl_pipeline_verified`.\n\nSummary of the ETL Stage 3 OOM diagnosis and fix:\n\n1. **Failure identified**: `etl-job` failed with `[INVALID_DRIVER_MEMORY] System memory 259522560 must be at least 471859200` — the 256m driver/executor memory was below Spark's hard minimum.\n2. **Root cause / data skew**: `diagnostic-server` and `data-generator`'s `/data/skew_info.txt` both confirmed `user_id=999` holds 50,000/100,000 records (~50%), a **skew_ratio=500x** — far above the 10x threshold, meaning Stage 3's `GROUP BY user_id` would OOM even with more headroom.\n3. **Fix applied**:\n   - Deleted the failing job and recreated it with `--driver-memory 1g` / `spark.executor.memory=1g` (up from 256m), plus `spark.sql.adaptive.enabled=true` and `spark.sql.adaptive.skewJoin.enabled=true` to address the underlying skew.\n   - Scaled `spark-worker` to 4 replicas and set `SPARK_WORKER_MEMORY=2G` for added parallelism/headroom.\n4. **Result**: `etl-job` now shows `Complete 1/1`, with clean logs and no OOM/memory errors.\n\nNote: as in the prior stage, the `etl-job.yaml` file referenced in the instructions isn't present in this session's filesystem, so I reconstructed the corrected Job manifest directly (same image, resources, service account) with the memory and AQE settings applied, then `kubectl apply`'d it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3011,"cache_read_input_tokens":101929,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3011},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"231e1989-0693-42c4-99a6-c53131